PTC Deliver THC with Intent to Deliver as repeater - Guilty plea.  Convicted.  Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years.  One (1) year initial confinement, to commence on 09-09-14 by 6:00 p.m., followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  
Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Full-time employment or job search combination;
4) Submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
5) Pay costs of action;
6) Provide DNA sample;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Defendant is given credit for 26 days time already served.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
